comments: Gordon (DEN) places his forearm to Tatum's (BOS) side moving along his path during his drive to the basket and lightly brushes Tatum's arm during his dunk attempt.
Brown (BOS) is moving alongside Murray's (DEN) path and marginal body contact occurs during Murray's drive.
Jokic's (DEN) shot attempt does not make contact with the rim and the shot clock expires.
Tatum (BOS) is out of bounds when he makes contact with the ball.  Since he never gains possession, the shot clock is not reset.
Porter Jr. (DEN) brings his arm toward Tatum's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs during Tatum's drive.
Porzingis (BOS) jumps into Jokic's (DEN) body and dislodges him from his position in order to get to the ball.
Brown (BOS) and Murray (DEN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Porzingis (BOS) briefly grasps Gordon's (DEN) arm and releases when Gordon gains possession of the rebound.
Brown (BOS) places his hands at Murray's (DEN) sides as he is moving forward and the contact quickly dissolves.
Porzingis (BOS) and Porter Jr. (DEN) mutually engage and immediately disengage during the rebound.
Jokic (DEN) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball during Tatum's (BOS) drive.
White (BOS) commits a take foul on Gordon (DEN).
Porzingis (BOS), Jokic (DEN), and Brown (BOS) all step into the lane before the release of the free throw.
Porzingis (BOS) briefly places his left arm around Jokic's (DEN) right arm as he prepares to elevate for the jump ball, but immediately removes it.
Boston signals for and is awarded the timeout prior to any possible foul by Jokic (DEN) on Holiday (BOS).
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) and Tatum (BOS) engage and immediately disengage with one another.

Tatum (BOS) extends his right leg as part of his jump shot attempt and any contact by Caldwell-Pope (DEN) is marginal.  He steps on Tatum's left foot planted on the floor as he is falling to the floor and the contact is incidental.
